<p>
  Here is a question that sounds simple but reveals a lot: how well do you know your partner? Not just the basics — their birthday, their coffee order, the name of their childhood pet. The real stuff. What keeps them up at night. What makes them feel most alive. The dream they stopped talking about but never actually let go of. Most couples overestimate how well they know each other. A study published in the Journal of Experimental Social Psychology found that the longer people are together, the more they assume they understand their partner — while their actual accuracy stays flat or even declines. Familiarity breeds confidence, not necessarily knowledge.
</p>

<p>
